Installation:
1. Install gvim
2. Install git
3. Windows: xcopy xcopy [git dir]\bin\libiconv-2.dll libexec\git-core\
4. copy ssh public key to .ssh

Create directory:
mkdir ~/.vim
mkdir c:\users\user_name\.vim (in Windows 7)

git clone git://github.com/O
Create directory:
mkdir ~/.vim
mkdir c:\users\user_name\.vim (in Windows 7)

git clone git://github.com/Oletros/dotvim.git
Create symlinks:

ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc (para sistemas Unix)
mklink c:\users\user_name\_vimrc c:\users\user_name\.vim\vimrc (in Windows 7)
ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc
mklink c:\users\user_name\_gvimrc c:\users\user_name\.vim\gvimrc (in Windows 7)
ln -s ~/.vim/tags/ctags.cnf ~/.ctags
mklink c:\users\user_name\ctags.cnf c:\users\user_name\.vim\ctags\ctags.cnf (in Windows 7)

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

cd ~/.vim
git submodule init
git submodule update

Original: http://vimcasts.org/episodes/synchronizing-plugins-with-git-submodules-and-pathogen/
vimrc: https://github.com/spf13/spf13-vim (no se por que no viene como subm√≥dulo)
